'''Anton F. Fahne''' (February 28, 1805 – January 12, 1883) was a German author, jurist, genealogist and historian.

Fahne was born in [[Münster]] and studied medicine at the [[University of Bonn]] and law at the [[Humboldt University of Berlin]]. He produced several genealogical and local historical writings. Fahne helped to found the Historischen Verein für den Niederrhein (Historical Society of the Lower Rhine) in 1854.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deutsche-biographie.de/sfz14121.html#adbcontent|last=Schell|first=Otto|website=[[Allgemeine Deutsche Biographie]]|access-date=2017-05-21}}</ref>

Fahne died in [[Düsseldorf]]. He was buried at the Gerresheimer Waldfriedhof in [[Düsseldorf-Gerresheim]]. His estate manages the [[Historical Archive of the City of Cologne]].

It is a common mistake that Anton Fahne and [[Friedrich von Uechtritz]] are the same person.

